# Pneumonia Detection Model (Google Colab)

A deep-learningâ€“based medical image classification project designed to detect pneumonia from chest X-ray images.  
This repository contains the complete workflow executed in **Google Colab**, including data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment-ready outputs.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

Pneumonia diagnosis through chest X-rays is time-consuming and prone to human error.  
This project builds a **Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)** trained on the popular **Chest X-Ray Pneumonia Dataset** (Kaggle), enabling automated and reliable detection of pneumonia.

The workflow is optimized for Google Colab (GPU-enabled) to ensure accessible and efficient training.

